	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For the triangle, the counter simply freezes. For the noise, I dunno...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Thu Apr 07, 2005 7:28 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Writing to $400b doesn't reset the phase of the triangle (it can't be reset).
<br />
<br />Writing to $400f doesn't reset the noise shift register (it can't be reset).
<br />
<br />For further information about defining things in terms of what isn't, rather than what is, refer to <a href="http://home.ripway.com/2003-7/16921/deviation.mp3" class="postlink">a short tutorial on deviation</a> (300K mp3).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


